k8s controller written in go!

Uses the client-go library to talk to the kubernetes cluster

This application can monitor the statuses of pods running in other namespaces in the same cluster

To deploy, run 
kubectl apply -f deployment.yaml -n=<namespace>

The docker image of the project gets uploaded to local docker registry on localhost:5000. When instances of this application are launched into k8s, it pulls the required image from that local registry.

How to upload a docker image to a local registry:
https://gravitydevops.com/how-to-create-local-repo-in-docker-and-push-and-pull-images/